05Dt 31:23 The LORD gave this command to Joshua son of Nun£º "Be strong and courageous, for you will bring the Israelites into the land I promised them on oath, and I myself will be with you."
05Dt 31:24 After Moses finished writing in a book the words of this law from beginning to end,
05Dt 31:25 he gave this command to the Levites who carried the ark of the covenant of the LORD£º
05Dt 31:26 "Take this Book of the Law and place it beside the ark of the covenant of the LORD your God. There it will remain as a witness against you.
05Dt 31:27 For I know how rebellious and stiff-necked you are. If you have been rebellious against the LORD while I am still alive and with you, how much more will you rebel after I die!
05Dt 31:28 Assemble before me all the elders of your tribes and all your officials, so that I can speak these words in their hearing and call heaven and earth to testify against them.
