091Sm 19:4 Jonathan spoke well of David to Saul his father and said to him, "Let not the king do wrong to his servant David; he has not wronged you, and what he has done has benefited you greatly.
091Sm 19:5 He took his life in his hands when he killed the Philistine. The LORD won a great victory for all Israel, and you saw it and were glad. Why then would you do wrong to an innocent man like David by killing him for no reason?"
091Sm 19:6 Saul listened to Jonathan and took this oath£º "As surely as the LORD lives, David will not be put to death."
091Sm 19:7 So Jonathan called David and told him the whole conversation. He brought him to Saul, and David was with Saul as before.
091Sm 19:8 Once more war broke out, and David went out and fought the Philistines. He struck them with such force that they fled before him.
091Sm 19:9 But an evil spirit from the LORD came upon Saul as he was sitting in his house with his spear in his hand. While David was playing the harp,
091Sm 19:10 Saul tried to pin him to the wall with his spear, but David eluded him as Saul drove the spear into the wall. That night David made good his escape.
091Sm 19:11 Saul sent men to David's house to watch it and to kill him in the morning. But Michal, David's wife, warned him, "If you don't run for your life tonight, tomorrow you'll be killed."
