091Sm 19:13 Then Michal took an idol and laid it on the bed, covering it with a garment and putting some goats' hair at the head.
091Sm 19:14 When Saul sent the men to capture David, Michal said, "He is ill."
091Sm 19:15 Then Saul sent the men back to see David and told them, "Bring him up to me in his bed so that I may kill him."
091Sm 19:16 But when the men entered, there was the idol in the bed, and at the head was some goats' hair.
091Sm 19:17 Saul said to Michal, "Why did you deceive me like this and send my enemy away so that he escaped?" Michal told him, "He said to me, 'Let me get away. Why should I kill you?'"
091Sm 19:18 When David had fled and made his escape, he went to Samuel at Ramah and told him all that Saul had done to him. Then he and Samuel went to Naioth and stayed there.
091Sm 19:19 Word came to Saul£º "David is in Naioth at Ramah";
091Sm 19:20 so he sent men to capture him. But when they saw a group of prophets prophesying, with Samuel standing there as their leader, the Spirit of God came upon Saul's men and they also prophesied.
091Sm 19:21 Saul was told about it, and he sent more men, and they prophesied too. Saul sent men a third time, and they also prophesied.
091Sm 19:22 Finally, he himself left for Ramah and went to the great cistern at Secu. And he asked, "Where are Samuel and David?" "Over in Naioth at Ramah," they said.
091Sm 19:23 So Saul went to Naioth at Ramah. But the Spirit of God came even upon him, and he walked along prophesying until he came to Naioth.
091Sm 19:24 He stripped off his robes and also prophesied in Samuel's presence. He lay that way all that day and night. This is why people say, "Is Saul also among the prophets?"
091Sm 20:1 Then David fled from Naioth at Ramah and went to Jonathan and asked, "What have I done? What is my crime? How have I wronged your father, that he is trying to take my life?"
091Sm 20:2 "Never!" Jonathan replied. "You are not going to die! Look, my father doesn't do anything, great or small, without confiding in me. Why would he hide this from me? It's not so!"
091Sm 20:3 But David took an oath and said, "Your father knows very well that I have found favor in your eyes, and he has said to himself, 'Jonathan must not know this or he will be grieved.' Yet as surely as the LORD lives and as you live, there is only a step between me and death."
091Sm 20:4 Jonathan said to David, "Whatever you want me to do, I'll do for you."
091Sm 20:5 So David said, "Look, tomorrow is the New Moon festival, and I am supposed to dine with the king; but let me go and hide in the field until the evening of the day after tomorrow.
091Sm 20:6 If your father misses me at all, tell him, 'David earnestly asked my permission to hurry to Bethlehem, his hometown, because an annual sacrifice is being made there for his whole clan.'
091Sm 20:7 If he says, 'Very well,' then your servant is safe. But if he loses his temper, you can be sure that he is determined to harm me.
091Sm 20:8 As for you, show kindness to your servant, for you have brought him into a covenant with you before the LORD. If I am guilty, then kill me yourself! Why hand me over to your father?"
091Sm 20:9 "Never!" Jonathan said. "If I had the least inkling that my father was determined to harm you, wouldn't I tell you?"
091Sm 20:10 David asked, "Who will tell me if your father answers you harshly?"
091Sm 20:11 "Come," Jonathan said, "let's go out into the field." So they went there together.
091Sm 20:12 Then Jonathan said to David£º "By the LORD, the God of Israel, I will surely sound out my father by this time the day after tomorrow! If he is favorably disposed toward you, will I not send you word and let you know?
091Sm 20:13 But if my father is inclined to harm you, may the LORD deal with me, be it ever so severely, if I do not let you know and send you away safely. May the LORD be with you as he has been with my father.
091Sm 20:14 But show me unfailing kindness like that of the LORD as long as I live, so that I may not be killed,
091Sm 20:15 and do not ever cut off your kindness from my family--not even when the LORD has cut off every one of David's enemies from the face of the earth."
091Sm 20:16 So Jonathan made a covenant with the house of David, saying, "May the LORD call David's enemies to account."
091Sm 20:17 And Jonathan had David reaffirm his oath out of love for him, because he loved him as he loved himself.
091Sm 20:18 Then Jonathan said to David£º "Tomorrow is the New Moon festival. You will be missed, because your seat will be empty.
091Sm 20:19 The day after tomorrow, toward evening, go to the place where you hid when this trouble began, and wait by the stone Ezel.
