102Sm 1:5 Then David said to the young man who brought him the report, "How do you know that Saul and his son Jonathan are dead?"
102Sm 1:6 "I happened to be on Mount Gilboa," the young man said, "and there was Saul, leaning on his spear, with the chariots and riders almost upon him.
102Sm 1:7 When he turned around and saw me, he called out to me, and I said, 'What can I do?'
102Sm 1:8 "He asked me, 'Who are you?' "'An Amalekite,' I answered.
