102Sm 1:13 David said to the young man who brought him the report, "Where are you from?" "I am the son of an alien, an Amalekite," he answered.
102Sm 1:14 David asked him, "Why were you not afraid to lift your hand to destroy the LORD'S anointed?"
102Sm 1:15 Then David called one of his men and said, "Go, strike him down!" So he struck him down, and he died.
102Sm 1:16 For David had said to him, "Your blood be on your own head. Your own mouth testified against you when you said, 'I killed the LORD'S anointed.'"
102Sm 1:17 David took up this lament concerning Saul and his son Jonathan,
102Sm 1:18 and ordered that the men of Judah be taught this lament of the bow (it is written in the Book of Jashar)£º
102Sm 1:19 "Your glory, O Israel, lies slain on your heights. How the mighty have fallen!
